summary: This is an FBI 302 form documenting a proffer interview conducted on August 28, 2019, at the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York. The interview was attended by multiple law enforcement officials, and the document notes the presence of attached interview notes. It is an official record of information provided by an interviewee under a proffer agreement.

events.title: Proffer Interview at SDNY
events.description: A proffer interview was conducted at the United States Attorneys Office of the Southern District of New York in New York, New York, pursuant to a proffer agreement.

events.title: FBI 302 Document Drafted
events.description: The FBI 302 form documenting the proffer interview was drafted.

locations: United States Attorneys Office of the Southern District of New York, New York, New York
keyFacts: A proffer interview was conducted on August 28, 2019, in New York City as part of an investigation.
The interview was attended by an Assistant United States Attorney (AUSA), an FBI Special Agent (SA), a Task Force Officer Detective, and an Inspector General (OIG) SA.
The FBI 302 form was drafted on September 23, 2019, and is an official record loaned to an agency with restrictions on distribution.
The document references attached notes taken by an AUSA during the interview.
All individual names in the document appear to be redacted or represented by placeholders.
